Class Coc

java.lang.Object
com.hhstechgroup.common.BaseActions
com.hhstechgroup.common.Coc
public class Coc
extends BaseActions
This class supports the creation, population and navigation of Provider Change Of Circumstance (CoC) requests.

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    void changeTheAddressForCoC​(java.lang.String enrollmentType)
    This method populates the Mailing Address Contact Person Middle Name displayed on the COC Address Details tab, then clicks 'Go to Change of Circumstance' (All enrollmentType arguments).
    void checkInvalidDataEmailsInCoc()
    This method checks for the value 'INVALID DATA' in the Mailing Address Contact Person Details section Email field on the Address Details tab and replaces the value with with a proper email address if found.
    void clickOnAddCOCButton()
    This method clicks the '+Add Change of Circumstance' button displayed on the CoC page.
    void cocAddKeyPersonnel()
    This method adds an entry to the Key Personnel table displayed on the Key Personnel tab and submits the CoC.
    void cocAddLicenseInformation​(java.lang.String enrollmentType, int index)
    This method adds an entry to the license table displayed on the CoC Taxonomy/License Information tab, adds a document to the CoC Upload Documents tab and submits the CoC.
    void cocAddressDetails()
    This method populates the Mailing Address on the COC Address Details tab with a SmartyStreets verified address and submits the CoC request (Regression version).
    void cocAddressDetails​(java.lang.String cocAddress)
    This method populates the Mailing Address on the COC Address Details tab with the cocAddress argument, selects the SmartyStreets verified address and submits the CoC request (Sanity version).
    void cocAlternateEmail​(java.lang.String emailPrefix, java.lang.String domain)  
    void cocIdentifyingInformation()
    This method populates the Provider Middle Name on the COC Identifying Information tab with a randomly generated name and submits the CoC request (Individual, ORP, PEM Enrollment Types).
    void cocIdentifyingInformationGeneratedName()
    This method populates the Provider Name on the COC Identifying Information tab with a randomly generated name and submits the CoC request (Group, Facility, Pharmacy Enrollment Types).
    void cocProviderIdentifier()  
    void cocProviderKeyPersonnel​(int index, java.lang.String employeeType)  
    void cocRequestForRetroActive​(java.lang.String date)  
    void createCoc​(java.lang.String cocType)
    This method clicks 'Next' on the CoC selection popup, selects the CoC category based on cocType argument, then clicks 'Create'
    void createCoCForEnrollment​(java.lang.String enrollmentType)
    This method clicks 'Next' on the CoC selection popup, selects the 'Address Details' category, then clicks 'Create' (PEM, Individual, Group, Facility enrollmentType arguments) OR selects the 'Address Details' category on the CoC selection popup, then clicks 'Create' (ORP, Pharmacy enrollmentType arguments).
    void createCoCForEnrollment​(java.lang.String enrollmentType, java.lang.String textOfButton)
    This method clicks 'Next' on the CoC selection popup, selects the 'Address Details' category, then clicks 'Create' (PEM, Individual, Group, Facility enrollmentType arguments) OR selects the 'Address Details' category on the CoC selection popup, then clicks 'Create' (ORP, Pharmacy enrollmentType arguments).
    void fillInAddressChangesInCocForm​(java.lang.String enrollmentType)
    This method populates the Mailing Address Contact Person Middle Name displayed on the COC Address Details tab and submits the CoC request (Individual, Group, Facility, ORP enrollmentType arguments) OR clicks Yes for 'Is Billing Address same as Mailing Address?' displayed on the COC Address Details tab and submits the CoC request (PEM, Pharmacy enrollmentType arguments).
    void fillInIdentifyingInCocFormPEM()
    This method populates the Provider First Name and Last Name on the COC Identifying Information tab with randomly generated names and submits the CoC request (PEM Enrollment Type).
    java.lang.String getProviderCoCID()
    This method retrieves the CoC Request ID from a CoC request listed on the Change of Circumstance Request History
    void navigateToCoCTabAndClickCoCButton()
    This method clicks the CoC link displayed on the menu bar, then clicks the '+Add Change of Circumstance' button displayed on the CoC page.
    void uploadSupportingDocuments()
    This method uploads a document on the COC Upload Documents tab and submits the CoC request.
